en_678950_0	Colombo (News1st) –  The New Deputy Speaker of Parliament will be appointed on Tuesday the 5th of June.
en_678950_1	Deputy General Secretary of Parliament, Neil Iddawela said the resignation of Former Deputy Speaker, Thilanga Sumathipala will be officially informed to Parliament, on that day.
en_678950_2	16 Parliamentarians including MP Thilanga Sumathipala defected from the government after voting in favor of the Motion of No Confidence against Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe.
en_678950_3	Accordingly, MP Thilanga Sumathipala informed that he will also resign from his post as Deputy Speaker.
